5|$|Legally, {{both the}} European Central Bank and the <b>central</b> <b>banks</b> of the eurozone {{countries}} {{have the right}} to issue the 7 different euro banknotes. In practice, only the national <b>central</b> <b>banks</b> of the zone physically issue and withdraw euro banknotes. The European Central Bank does not have a cash office and is not involved in any cash operations.|$|E
