5|$|On 30 November 2011, the ECB, the US Federal Reserve, the <b>central</b> <b>banks</b> of Canada, Japan, Britain and the Swiss National Bank {{provided}} {{global financial}} markets with additional liquidity {{to ward off}} the debt crisis and to support the real economy. The <b>central</b> <b>banks</b> agreed to lower the cost of dollar currency swaps by 50 basis points to come into effect on 5 December 2011. They also agreed to provide each other with abundant liquidity to make sure that commercial banks stay liquid in other currencies.|$|E
